-- Royals’ Tejada Suspended 105 Games by MLB for Amphetamine Use
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-08-17T18:37:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-17/royals-tejada-suspended-105-games-by-mlb-for-amphetamine-use.html
Kansas City Royals infielder Miguel
Tejada was suspended for 105 games by Major League Baseball
after testing positive for an amphetamine.  The office of Major League Baseball Commissioner  Bud Selig 
announced the suspension, which begins immediately, in a
statement.  Tejada, 39, won the American League’s Most Valuable Player
Award in 2002 while playing for the Oakland Athletics.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  